<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 31 at 6:43PM MDT until May 31 at 7:00PM MDT by NWS Boulder</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 700 PM MDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN MORGAN COUNTY...
At 642 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Antelope
Springs, or 12 miles north of Fort Morgan, moving north at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Antelope Springs and Snyder.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
